{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01BxfP8jQ2zWLoCfgvrnpPun","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019dzpcfzoVMU2aD5PCL45zb","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/findings.txt","content":"CockroachDB Compliance Configuration Audit\n==========================================\nNamespace: cockroachdb   StatefulSet: crdb-cluster\nAudit type: READ-ONLY (no changes made to the live cluster)\nDate: 2026-06-18\n\n1. CLUSTER TOPOLOGY & HEALTH\n----------------------------\n- Nodes: 3 (crdb-cluster-0/1/2), all live and available.\n- StatefulSet crdb-cluster: 3/3 replicas Ready, all pods Running, 0 restarts.\n- CockroachDB build: v24.1.0 (cluster version 24.1). Deployment is --insecure.\n- No regions/locality configured (single-region, empty locality strings).\n- Range health: 69 ranges total, 0 unavailable, 66 under-replicated.\n  -> The high under-replicated count is EXPECTED, not a fault: several system\n     zones request num_replicas=5 (see section 3) but only 3 nodes exist, so\n     those ranges cannot reach 5 replicas. No data is at risk (0 unavailable).\n- Databases present: defaultdb, postgres, system (no user databases, no custom\n  database-level zone configs).\n\n2. NON-DEFAULT CLUSTER SETTINGS\n-------------------------------\n- kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 1.0 MiB   (default 32 MiB)  <-- TUNED DOWN\n    Rebalance/snapshot throughput throttled to 1 MiB/s (32x below default).\n    Slows data movement during rebalancing / node maintenance.\n- diagnostics.reporting.enabled = true (default true; reported as set).\n- cluster.secret = 018f15f6-8480-4198-8fcf-a41dbf5cb4c7 (auto-generated, n/a).\n- version = 24.1 (cluster version marker).\n- No sql.defaults.* settings differ from their defaults.\n- kv.snapshot_recovery.max_rate = 32 MiB (default, unchanged).\n\n3. ZONE CONFIGURATIONS (replication factor & GC TTL)\n----------------------------------------------------\nDefault replication factor for user data (RANGE default): num_replicas = 3.\n\nCustom / elevated zone configs in place:\n  RANGE default   : num_replicas=3, gc.ttlseconds=14400 (4h),\n                    range_min=128MiB, range_max=512MiB\n  RANGE system    : num_replicas=5, gc.ttlseconds=14400 (4h)\n  RANGE meta      : num_replicas=5, gc.ttlseconds=3600 (1h)\n  RANGE liveness  : num_replicas=5, gc.ttlseconds=600 (10m)\n  DATABASE system : num_replicas=5, gc.ttlseconds=14400 (4h),\n                    range_min=128MiB, range_max=512MiB\n\nPer-table GC TTL overrides on system tables:\n  system.public.lease                          : gc.ttlseconds=600  (10m)\n  system.public.replication_constraint_stats   : gc.ttlseconds=600  (10m)\n  system.public.replication_stats              : gc.ttlseconds=600  (10m)\n  system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries   : gc.ttlseconds=3600 (1h)\n  system.public.statement_activity             : gc.ttlseconds=3600 (1h)\n  system.public.statement_statistics           : gc.ttlseconds=3600 (1h)\n  system.public.tenant_usage                   : gc.ttlseconds=7200 (2h)\n  system.public.transaction_activity           : gc.ttlseconds=3600 (1h)\n  system.public.transaction_statistics         : gc.ttlseconds=3600 (1h)\n\nNo constraints or lease_preferences are set on any zone (all empty).\n\n4. NON-DEFAULT TUNING SUMMARY (for compliance review)\n-----------------------------------------------------\na. Snapshot rebalance rate throttled to 1 MiB/s (kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate)\n   -> recovery/rebalancing will be slow; consider impact on the maintenance\n      window (node drains may take longer than usual).\nb. System metadata ranges over-provisioned at 5 replicas (system, meta,\n   liveness, database system) on a 3-node cluster -> permanently under-replicated\n   until cluster is grown to >=5 nodes. Acceptable for durability, but flagged.\nc. GC TTLs shortened from CRDB defaults on system/internal tables and ranges\n   (down to 10m on liveness/lease/replication-stats). Shorter recovery window\n   for AS OF SYSTEM TIME / time-travel on those objects.\n\n5. MAINTENANCE-WINDOW NOTES\n---------------------------\n- Only 3 nodes: a single node drain temporarily removes 1/3 of capacity and\n  cannot satisfy num_replicas=5 system zones during the window.\n- Throttled snapshot rate (1 MiB/s) means re-replication after a node restart\n  will be slow; allow extra time before declaring the window complete.\n\nEnd of audit. The live cluster was inspected read-only and left unchanged.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1208,"cache_read_input_tokens":30740,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1208},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2b5b9707-90e4-4d92-a847-4dff74157622","uuid":"6a38db63-969a-4467-95f8-3584180f5ee1","request_id":"req_011CcAp9XKpoDo1nnLx7bKYd"}
